This paper is primarily focused on reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of options, which are a common technique in hierarchical reinforcement learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also discusses exploration efficiency, which is a common topic in robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. The experiments conducted in the paper are in the Atari environment, which involves visual inputs, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible category as well. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of a high-level policy and a low-level policy, which is a common technique in control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category.
